de setup guidance**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the guidance for test code setup, especially related to setting system properties. If there's a need for local temporary repository setup, I should include that in the agent guidance. I’ll opt for no action unless there’s solid evidence that more setup is needed. The issue with failing compilations might not require additional steps since meaningful coverage can be achieved without them. If the agent wants to perform git operations, that’s more typical test code rather than a global setup. I should return no action but note that tests must have git in the PATH.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hW0MNOgm1iVuZEehf0S6BD8T|fc_04f34ec1e5489b29016a2a6c3adf10819485f406da944656c2", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=/tmp/tmp.6hbBMhUul0; rg -n \"gitexe|git executable|Git Executable|command line|provider implementation|git command|GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT|maven.scm\" \"$tmp/rel/maven-scm-2.2.1\"/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git \"$tmp/rel/maven-scm-2.2.1\"/src/site 2>/dev/null | head -200", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 13269, "output": 524, "cacheRead": 45568, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59361, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781165095841, "responseId": "resp_04f34ec1e5489b29016a2a6c286fb88194b0776c5af59f2b9a"}}
