er/consumer, repository URL, and provider behavior tests using local temporary files without additional Maven dependencies, Docker services, or required system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Tests that execute real Git operations instead of only constructing/parsing commands will rely on a `git` executable on `PATH` and may need local temporary-repository configuration such as `user.name` and `user.email`; that is test-code setup, not driver-level deterministic setup.\",\n    \"The reported javac failure is caused by Maven SCM 2.2.1 API changes such as `GitTagCommand.createCommandLine` now taking `CommandParameters.SignOption` and `createPushCommandLine` being instance-based, not by missing setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04f34ec1e5489b29016a2a6c4ddd0481948c0af7c632509355\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 15714, "output": 734, "cacheRead": 58368, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 74816, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781165115588, "responseId": "resp_04f34ec1e5489b29016a2a6c3c4760819486bc595b962549eb"}}
